WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.440 --> 00:00:01.440
Hello.

2
00:00:02.360 --> 00:00:06.480
To install CaseTrace, go to
casetrace.dk. Press download.

3
00:00:07.870 --> 00:00:08.910
It downloads the program.

4
00:00:09.270 --> 00:00:10.750
I have already downloaded it.

5
00:00:11.610 --> 00:00:13.356
Then you install in
the language you want.

6
00:00:13.380 --> 00:00:14.200
Press next.

7
00:00:14.350 --> 00:00:15.350
Install it.

8
00:00:15.590 --> 00:00:17.510
I'm canceling here
because I already have it.

9
00:00:18.080 --> 00:00:19.960
Then you open the program CaseTrace.

10
00:00:20.670 --> 00:00:22.070
Then I will show how it works.

11
00:00:22.960 --> 00:00:26.000
There are activities that log
everything you do on your computer.

12
00:00:26.970 --> 00:00:28.680
Then you have folder time,
which is probably interesting.

13
00:00:29.940 --> 00:00:32.060
Here you can go in and add a folder.

14
00:00:32.180 --> 00:00:33.180
I add show.

15
00:00:34.990 --> 00:00:39.080
So when I have added a show, I
can, for example, give it a budget.

16
00:00:40.520 --> 00:00:42.920
I can call that case number 1.

17
00:00:43.590 --> 00:00:47.000
And then say there are 10
hours and an hourly rate of 750.

18
00:00:48.540 --> 00:00:51.820
Now this entire folder
has a budget of DKK 7,500.

19
00:00:53.020 --> 00:00:54.020
and we have 10 hours.

20
00:00:54.980 --> 00:00:56.260
Then I will try to open the folder.

21
00:00:57.200 --> 00:00:58.200
In here in the folder.

22
00:00:58.680 --> 00:00:59.680
I have two folders there.

23
00:00:59.900 --> 00:01:00.900
This one is empty.

24
00:01:02.140 --> 00:01:03.180
There is a file here.

25
00:01:04.120 --> 00:01:04.980
A text file.

26
00:01:05.140 --> 00:01:06.440
We are trying to open the text file.

27
00:01:07.660 --> 00:01:09.540
It's just to test.

28
00:01:10.480 --> 00:01:11.600
As soon as I open it.

29
00:01:12.120 --> 00:01:14.220
Then you can see the
program here starts to log.

30
00:01:15.390 --> 00:01:17.120
It's open right now and
it's counting seconds.

31
00:01:18.590 --> 00:01:23.360
When it counts up enough, it shows
how much money you have spent

32
00:01:23.510 --> 00:01:25.500
out of the 7500 and how much time
you have spent out of the 10 hours.

33
00:01:26.610 --> 00:01:28.090
And it also gives you notifications.

34
00:01:32.120 --> 00:01:35.660
I have already made two folders here.

35
00:01:36.360 --> 00:01:37.220
As I have added below.

36
00:01:37.300 --> 00:01:38.300
You can remove them again.

37
00:01:39.140 --> 00:01:40.180
There is one called test.

38
00:01:41.620 --> 00:01:44.120
Where I have some different
folders with subfolders.

39
00:01:44.450 --> 00:01:47.420
It even finds the subfolders
every time you open a document.

40
00:01:49.170 --> 00:01:51.880
Here you can see that I
have customer number 10.

41
00:01:52.140 --> 00:01:52.900
Case X.

42
00:01:53.060 --> 00:01:54.360
And there I have used 19%.

43
00:01:57.630 --> 00:01:58.910
And here is a folder with 19%.

44
00:01:59.135 --> 00:02:05.000
So you can also put a budget on
the subfolders if that's what you want.

45
00:02:07.120 --> 00:02:11.860
In addition, we still have a program that
logs all files you open on your computer.

46
00:02:12.440 --> 00:02:14.580
How many times each file has been opened.

47
00:02:14.700 --> 00:02:16.000
And for what period of time.

48
00:02:17.080 --> 00:02:18.580
And you can go in and
look in the dashboard.

49
00:02:18.940 --> 00:02:21.100
How many hours you spent in your day.

50
00:02:22.140 --> 00:02:23.460
Then you can go into settings.

51
00:02:24.580 --> 00:02:25.620
Sorry, help.

52
00:02:26.120 --> 00:02:28.620
In here you can make a database backup.

53
00:02:30.210 --> 00:02:32.760
You can see when it
needs to make a backup.

54
00:02:34.090 --> 00:02:35.610
In which days or hours and minutes.

55
00:02:35.680 --> 00:02:37.000
How many backups there should be.

56
00:02:37.510 --> 00:02:38.200
And then they are down here.

57
00:02:38.280 --> 00:02:39.320
So you always have a backup.

58
00:02:39.840 --> 00:02:42.080
You can store the backup
on OneDrive if you want.

59
00:02:42.960 --> 00:02:44.120
Or locally on your computer.

60
00:02:45.600 --> 00:02:46.740
Last but not least.

61
00:02:46.815 --> 00:02:49.460
Then we have billable hours per day.

62
00:02:49.660 --> 00:02:50.600
Here we can go in.

63
00:02:50.660 --> 00:02:51.960
So we'll just start today.

64
00:02:52.710 --> 00:02:53.870
Then we can print here as a PDF.

65
00:02:55.780 --> 00:02:56.900
Then it pops up here.

66
00:02:59.650 --> 00:03:01.650
Then we can see that these are
the hours we saw inside folder time.

67
00:03:02.280 --> 00:03:03.600
Here are the hours used.

68
00:03:05.785 --> 00:03:07.220
They are then inside the document.

69
00:03:11.480 --> 00:03:14.820
We also have up here, you
can see we have 3 folders.

70
00:03:15.840 --> 00:03:17.440
And 3 files have been selected in total.

71
00:03:17.520 --> 00:03:20.180
And we have spent 10
minutes and 9 seconds in total.

72
00:03:22.350 --> 00:03:23.920
If you enter the menu.

73
00:03:24.600 --> 00:03:25.600
And press settings.

74
00:03:25.920 --> 00:03:27.520
And then press show today's overview.

75
00:03:28.360 --> 00:03:30.180
So every morning when
the computer turns on.

76
00:03:30.260 --> 00:03:33.900
Then what you have spent the most
time in folder time comes up here.

77
00:03:34.240 --> 00:03:36.800
And in activities what
you spent the most time on.

78
00:03:37.750 --> 00:03:40.700
It's just a little quick
informational info.

79
00:03:42.880 --> 00:03:44.780
And then we have the new one over here.

80
00:03:44.860 --> 00:03:46.060
It's called unallocated time.

81
00:03:46.910 --> 00:03:50.340
It is simply the time
you spend on files.

82
00:03:51.050 --> 00:03:53.320
Which is not in folder time.

83
00:03:53.970 --> 00:03:55.250
It could be some other things.

84
00:03:56.150 --> 00:03:57.420
It could be anything.

85
00:03:57.575 --> 00:04:00.280
Then you can simply go in and assign.

86
00:04:01.110 --> 00:04:03.216
If you have done
something special.

87
00:04:03.240 --> 00:04:04.740
But it is not during the folder time.

88
00:04:04.820 --> 00:04:05.820
Then you can assign it.

89
00:04:07.410 --> 00:04:08.690
What case it should be under.

90
00:04:09.290 --> 00:04:11.276
Or what subfolder
if it's not in there.

91
00:04:11.300 --> 00:04:12.300
And then press OK.

92
00:04:14.140 --> 00:04:15.140
So we'll see here.

93
00:04:16.350 --> 00:04:17.460
Then it fell under here.

94
00:04:20.070 --> 00:04:21.670
And then the seconds also fell in there.

95
00:04:22.420 --> 00:04:23.420
Thank you for watching.
